public static class ImagePrototype.Data<T extends com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.system.SmugObjectData<?>>
extends com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.system.SmugObjectData<T>

Instances of this class hold the prototype-data for creation of Images-s.
This class also functions as a base-class for Image-s.

getImageData

public byte[] getImageData()
Returns the raw image-data as an array of bytes.
Note that after a successful ImagePrototype.create() or Image.update(), this method will return null. This is done to preserve memory.

Returns:
the raw image-data.

setImageData

public void setImageData(byte[] imgData)
Sets the raw image-data. It updates the MD5Sum and Size as well. If null, the image-data (and MD5Sum and Size) will be cleared. Note that after a successful ImagePrototype.create() or Image.update(), this attribute will be null. This is done to preserve memory.

Parameters:
imgData - The raw image-data.
